    "updated_at": "2024-03-09T21:29:47Z",
    "body": "@sabinonweb I believe the request is to add another rule in addition to the existing list of rules from your screen shot.\r\n\r\nThe new rule allows you to specify a list of usernames in the starship configuration. If the active username matches any of the ones in the list of usernames, then do NOT display the module. Not sure what the property would be called in the configuration, but something like “excludeUsernames” or “noDisplayUsernames” is what I think of. \r\n\r\nA concrete example:\r\non my local computer and most of my machines that I log in to I use the username “mcompton13”, but there are a few that have other usernames like “ubuntu”. I would like starship to only display the “username@“ part of my prompt if the current username != mcompton13. ",
    "author_association": "NONE",
